\"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antoine_Dupont\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antoine_Dupont\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2-1/2 hour show will include a theatrical sequence entitled \\\"Records\\\", which promises a dream-like immersive journey through time, led by a \\\"Golden Voyager\\\".\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His odyssey begins at the origins of the Olympic Games before proceeding to a science-fiction filled dystopian future where the Olympic Games have vanished and must be rediscovered.\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Along the way, the voyager will discover the symbols of peace and unity than underpin the values of Olympism.\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1691, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it is the musicians and Eilish, Red Hot Chili Peppers and Snoop Dogg, the U.S. rapper who has been contributing to NBC Primetime's coverage of the Games, that will awe fans and television spectators.\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1755, \"end\": 1765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 1812, \"end\": 1815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999877948343016, \"rank\": 1.1915954462638149e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Grammy-winning artist H.E.R.\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 1926, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1920, \"end\": 1926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0060670612131933e-45, \"text\": \"H.E.R.\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"will perform the U.S. national anthem live in Paris, while rumours have swirled around Paris that Tom Cruise will perform a stunt worthy of Mission Impossible.\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 2086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1944, \"end\": 1964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"U.S. national anthem\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\"}, {\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.25332611946619e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2014, \"end\": 2019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.25332611946619e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2025, \"end\": 2035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}, {\"begin\": 2067, \"end\": 2085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Grohl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.466933179862488e-38, \"text\": \"Mission Impossible\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Grohl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Grohl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"FLAG TO PASS TO LA  \\\"This is the biggest moment in LA28 history to date, as the Olympic flag passes from Paris to LA,\\\" LA28 Chairperson and President Casey Wasserman said in a statement.\", \"from\": 2088, \"to\": 2274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2193, \"end\": 2198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.25332611946619e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2238, \"end\": 2253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Casey Wasserman\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A final unnamed star is also expected to perform and a version of Frank Sinatra's \\\"My Way\\\", originally sung by French musical icon Claude Francois, will end the show, perhaps a wink to the world that Paris did it its way.\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2342, \"end\": 2355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frank_Sinatra\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.653358023203833e-37, \"text\": \"Frank Sinatra\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frank_Sinatra\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frank_Sinatra\"}, {\"begin\": 2387, \"end\": 2393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.5621299705605034, \"rank\": 0.6654193777550096, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2407, \"end\": 2422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claude_Fran\\u00e7ois\", \"score\": 0.9999999337810572, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Claude Francois\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claude_Fran\\u00e7ois\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claude_Fran\\u00e7ois\"}, {\"begin\": 2476, \"end\": 2481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.25332611946619e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two weeks of sporting drama saw China and the United States duke it out for top spot in the medal table right down to the last event.\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2535, \"end\": 2540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999991301528244, \"rank\": 5.111369026048095e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2549, \"end\": 2562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999664978623064, \"rank\": 0.00033139188511127014, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Echoing the heartache delivered to France by the United States in the men's basketball final, the American women's basketball side handed France a gut-wrenching one-point defeat to earn a 40th gold medal and top spot on the medal table.\", \"from\": 2638, \"to\": 2874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2673, \"end\": 2679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9819031900729297, \"rank\": 0.018400006325544904, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2687, \"end\": 2700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999664978623064, \"rank\": 0.00033139188511127014, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2736, \"end\": 2744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999404071804, \"rank\": 5.581293626784413e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2776, \"end\": 2782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9819031900729297, \"rank\": 0.018400006325544904, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of the ceremony, fans praised France's handling of the Games and recounted a fortnight of sporting drama and Olympic spirit in packed-out venues at the heart of one of the world's most beautiful cities.\", \"from\": 2876, \"to\": 3084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2912, \"end\": 2918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9819031900729297, \"rank\": 0.018400006325544904, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think these were Games for the ages,\\\" said Adam Osprey, 60, a retired American civil servant who lives in France.\", \"from\": 3086, \"to\": 3202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3137, \"end\": 3143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Osprey\", \"score\": 0.9928099297101062, \"rank\": 0.007236677108267412, \"text\": \"Osprey\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Osprey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Osprey\"}, {\"begin\": 3159, \"end\": 3167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999404071804, \"rank\": 5.581293626784413e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3195, \"end\": 3201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9819031900729297, \"rank\": 0.018400006325544904, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"HIGH BAR  To the surprise of many French, a euphoric Olympic fever gripped the host nation during the Games.\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3238, \"end\": 3244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.5621299705605034, \"rank\": 0.6654193777550096, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French had a new golden boy to celebrate with swimmer Leon Marchand emerging as the king of the pool, winning four golds in the opening week, before French judoka Teddy Riner reigned supreme as he claimed his fifth Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3318, \"end\": 3324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.5621299705605034, \"rank\": 0.6654193777550096, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 3377, \"end\": 3385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9990706334153683, \"rank\": 0.0009294602935615895, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}, {\"begin\": 3467, \"end\": 3473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.5621299705605034, \"rank\": 0.6654193777550096, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 3481, \"end\": 3492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simone Biles put her twisties misery of Tokyo behind her, making a long-awaited Olympic return in front of a star-studded crowd.\", \"from\": 3554, \"to\": 3682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3594, \"end\": 3599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999412671204815, \"rank\": 0.00058767395302049, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She arrived the world's most decorated gymnast and left with a further four gold medals for her trophy cabinet.\", \"from\": 3683, \"to\": 3794, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking made its Olympic debut - to some derision on social media - whilst 3x3 basketball, sports climbing, skateboarding and surfing made their second appearances.\", \"from\": 3796, \"to\": 3961, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC will be relieved that no major scandals erupted, although it did have to grapple with some controversies.\", \"from\": 3963, \"to\": 4076, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3967, \"end\": 3970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.046386865879885e-38, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A simmering doping row involving Chinese athletes hung over the Olympic swimming meet where the United States faced the biggest challenge to their reign in decades.\", \"from\": 4078, \"to\": 4242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4174, \"end\": 4187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999664978623064, \"rank\": 0.00033139188511127014, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A storm around gender eligibility hit the women's boxing competition, revealing the toxic relations between the IOC and a widely discredited International Boxing Association.\", \"from\": 4244, \"to\": 4418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4356, \"end\": 4359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.046386865879885e-38, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 4385, \"end\": 4417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6816727785706754e-18, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, a $1.5 billion clean-up of the Seine rewarded Paris with the optics of triathlon and marathon swimmers competing in the river through central Paris, without a wave of illness ensuing - even if bacteria levels forced some training to be cancelled.\", \"from\": 4420, \"to\": 4677, \"entities\": [{\"begin\